July 8 at 2:05 PM ¬∑

Virtual Summer Reading Programming
Just for Kids (ages 5-12)

Quest Letter!
Imagine you are playing outside one day when a carrier pigeon drops a piece of rolled up paper onto your lap. You carefully unroll it. Inside it tells you that you must save the day! Write what you think the letter would say. Include who you are being called to save, why and what the journey will look like to get there.

When you are finished with the letter, stop by Youth Services at Main or the Pastrick Branch so that we can read your story! üôÇ

post_text:
ECUEA Families,

We understand that our families are eager to hear the details regarding our fall reopening plan. We are currently finalizing those details and will present it as soon as it is finalized. For consistency, our reentry plan may be similar to the plans of the rest of Lake County school districts and in conjunction with the East Chicago & Lake County Health Departments.

Thank you for your continued patience as we finalize details for a safe reentry for our students, staff and families. We look forward to welcoming our students and staff back to school on August 10th!

Indiana PTA
June 23 at 9:12 PM ¬∑

Indiana PTA - Free Virtual Trainings 2020: Register Now!

Indiana PTA has moved all back to school training sessions online for the start of the 2020-2021 school year. All units should plan to attend at least one of the following FREE virtual trainings to prepare for the upcoming year. Attendance will provide your PTA with valuable information, as well as satisfy the annual training requirement to be a Unit in Good Standing. All sessions will last approximately 90 minutes. Contact Indiana PTA at either Indianapta@sbcglobal.net or 317-357-5881 to reserve your place.

Back to School Training on PTA Basics:
June 22 @ 6 p.m. central / 7 p.m. est
July 8 @ 6 p.m. central / 7 p.m. est
August 13 @ 6 p.m. central / 7 p.m. est
Sept. 12 @ 1 p.m. central / 2 p.m. est
Sept. 29 @ 6 p.m. central / 7 p.m. est
October 8 @ 6 p.m. central / 7 p.m. est
Special Intensive Training for Treasurers:
July 23 @ 6 p.m central / 7 p.m. est - Open to all Units
August 25 @ 4:00 central / 5:00 est - Hammond Unit Treasurers
Sept. 22 @ 6 p.m. central / 7 p.m. est - Open to all Units

East Chicago Public Library
June 15 at 1:29 PM ¬∑

Juneteenth Fact:

Most people are familiar with the celebration and history behind the Fourth of July. However, when the United States became free in 1776, Black people weren‚Äôt freed from slavery at that time.

In fact, Black people were not declared free for another 87 years. And even still, it took an additional 2 years beyond Abraham Lincoln‚Äôs signing of the Emancipation Proclamation for the last slaves to be freed in Galveston, TX.

June 19, 1865 ‚Äì Juneteenth ‚Äì is the oldest nationally celebrated commemoration of the ending of slavery in the United States.

School City of East Chicago in conjunction with the City of East Chicago End of Year Parade. We ask everyone to decorate their home/yard and represent their school. Class of 2020 wear your cap and gown. The parade will travel throughout the City of East Chicago. Families do not go to the school. Approximate times for arrival at school/area: Harrison 10:30-10:45, McKinley 11:15-11:30, Washington 1:15-1:30, Block 1:30, Lincoln 1:45-2:00 and Carrie Gosch 2:30-2:45 Teachers may park in their school parking lot. March 20 at 3:30 PM ¬∑

Hello ECPL Patrons! As you all know both Main and Pastrick branches are closed to the public and scheduled to reopen on Monday, April 13th at 9am.

To help stop the spread of COVID-19, schools and libraries are closing across the country. ABDO wants to ensure that readers everywhere continue to have the opportunity to learn and grow during this unprecedented event.

The ABDO digital products are available for free now through June 2020.

For the Elementary Digital Bookshelf (Grades Pre K-8) Online Digital Library please click on this link:
https://abdodigital.com/?tk=414F33301B8E136DEE3F0A93BF1795E1

For the Secondary Digital Bookshelf (Grades 5-12) Online Digital Library please click on this link:
https://abdodigital.com/?tk=840BC558E6676AB1F4C9FA29D8EC6D69

You can also scan or select the QR codes (on this flyer below) for instant access to these free resources.

post_text: Mrs. DeVine is one of our students and families strongest advocates. She is dedicated to serving our students, our families and our school. She provides encouragement and support, while holding them accountable. Mrs. DeVine has also taken on additional roles such as community outreach and Heart & Sole coach. She has built many community ties which in turn have strengthened relationships & collaboration among those with a vested interest in the success of our youth. We hope that she knows how much we love and appreciate everything she does for us. Thank you, Mrs. DeVine, for all you do for our ECUEA family!
